notesStmt.note: Catalog entry, number 185, pasted into inside front cover with note in pencil "Sotheby's Feb. 1925".
Stamps and notes cover the front and back leaves (f. 1r, 292v-[293]v). Three stamps are legible: 1) ʻInayāt Allāh, 1130 A.H. ; 2) Ibrāhīm ; 3) Muḥammad Bāqir, 1110 A.H. (f. 292v).

msContents.summary: Copy of a Persian dictionary; folios 165-166 are adhered.

supportDesc.extent: 292, i leaves : 250 x 160 (170 x 90) mm bound to 250 x 160 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation added in pencil, upper left recto; catchwords every verso, lower left.

layoutDesc.layout: 19 long lines; ruled with a misṭarah.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in clear nastaʻlīq in black ink; pointed.

binding.p: Bound in brown leather over pasteboard (Type III) with gilt-stamped central mandorla and two pendants on the vertical axis; gilt-stamped frame; doublure of red leather with inset mandorla painted green, blue and orange with gold filigree and gold painted finials and frame.

origin.p: Copy completed in Muḥarram 1030 (December 1620) by Muḥammad Sabzavārī (f. 292v).

history.provenance: Formerly owned by Muḥammad Bāqir (note in ink with stamp, f. 292v).
Formerly owned by John Frederick Lewis.
